he correct diagnosis.</p></sec></body><back><ref-list><ref id="B1"><mixed-citation publication-type="book"><person-group person-group-type="editor">Pizzo and Poplack</person-group><source>Principles and Practice of Pediatric Oncology</source><edition>6</edition></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="B2"><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Meyer</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><name><surname>Nadel</surname><given-names>H</given-names></name><name><surname>Marina</surname><given-names>N</given-names></name><etal/><article-title>Response to &#x0201c;Imaging guidelines for children with Ewing sarcoma and osteosarcoma: A report from the Children's Oncology Group Bone Tumor Committee&#x0201d;</article-title><source>Pediatric Blood &#x00026; Cancer</source><year>2008</year><volume>51</volume><fpage>163</fpage><lpage>170</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1002/pbc.21596</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">18454470</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="B3"><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Mar</surname><given-names>WA</given-names></name><name><surname>Taljanovic</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name><name><surname>Bagatell</surname><given-names>R</given-names></name><etal/><article-title>Update on imaging and treatment of Ewing sarcoma family of tumors: What the radiologist needs to know</article-title><source>J Comput Assist Tomogr</source><year>2008</year><volume>32</volume><fpage>108</fpage><lpage>118</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1097/RCT.0b013e31805c030f</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">18303298</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="B4"><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Galindo</surname><given-names>C</given-names></name><name><surname>Shah</surname><given-names>N</given-names></name><name><surname>McCarville</surname><given-names>MB</given-names></name><etal/><article-title>Outcome after local recurrence of osteosarcoma</article-title><source>Cancer</source><year>2004</year><v